body:
@scucheri The Android TF library is inference only, so there is no training code to remove.

However, we include a large set of ops by default.  You can probably save quite a bit of space by using selective registration. This will strip the binary down to just the ops needed for your model pb. See [print_selective_registration_header.py](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/python/tools/print_selective_registration_header.py) for details.

Closing as this is neither a bug nor a feature request.
